The paper deals with the detection of AI-generated fake images, specifically DeepFakes, using a frequency domain analysis followed by a basic classifier. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep generative models, which falls under machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for automated ways to detect fake images, which falls under the cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of annotated training samples and achieving good accuracies in unsupervised scenarios, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
